You must first check the return value of `pldm_msgbuf_extract()` before doing any arithmetic with `req->length`. You need to know that the extraction succeeded, otherwise you're off in the weeds. This needs to be:

```
...
rc = pldm_msgbuf_extract(buf, req->length);
if (rc < 0) {
    return rc;
}

if ((req->length + ....) > req_length) {
    return -EBADMSG;
}
...
```

Thanks to your documentation I now understand what you're trying to do here. I think we can make some improvements.

If you move the definition of `struct pldm_oem_meta_file_io_read_data_info` above, we can instead have:

```
struct pldm_oem_meta_file_io_read_req {
    uint8_t handle;
    uint8_t read_option;
    union {
        struct pldm_oem_meta_file_io_read_data_info data;
    } info;
};
```

And then in the implementation of `decode_oem_meta_file_io_read_req()` you just unpack the message values directly using the provided value of `read_option`.

This should rather be set by the caller and checked by the implementation here:

```
if (req->version > sizeof(struct pldm_oem_meta_file_io_read_req)) {
    return -E2BIG;
}
```
